caption: The Jean Gabin Expo is a pure delight. For permanent collections of beautiful statues as well as beautiful paintings. I enjoyed wandering the 3 floors
It’s a very beautiful place on several floors. Surprising... thank you very much to the ladies at the reception. I really appreciated their friendliness, their availability and their kindness.
Very nice museum. The installation of the works is perfect for admiring them in good conditions. Smooth circulation, it's pleasant.
I loved learning more about the artist's work. I just think that many of the sculptures are close to the wall and could give us more chance to walk around and see them.
Splendid exhibition in a place where the staff takes great care of visitors.
Museum rather 2 museums Pleasant to visit Free the first Sunday of the month, however Few people in the morning.
Nickel, except that the nap sat down. Lying down is forbidden…..
Very beautiful museum, very pleasant on several floors. With the 1930s museum. Remarkable and little-known works. And of course Landowski masterpieces.
Too bad the entrance fee is so expensive

Very rich museum: sculptures, paintings, furniture...so many riches from this period and in perfect condition with full explanations from the museum guide...you have to come in the morning and have lunch to resume the visit. Lots of things to see, I also recommend the architectural models, Bravo!
Beautiful museum, very beautiful painting, but the receptionist understood absolutely nothing about the projects I wanted to carry out, spoke in vain and didn't let anyone speak.

On the occasion of the exhibition in tribute to Jean Gabin, I was able to appreciate the organization and a professional and warm welcome. The different objects and the screens retracing the actor's career are organized in such a way that the visit takes place in a very pleasant way. Well done and thank you to the whole team and a special satisfaction to Mr Mathias Moncorgé.

VERY unpleasant receptionist at the reception, if you stay too long in the museum hall she will look for her superior to kick you out, zero respect towards visitors and looks you up and down when you pass in front of her.
A must-visit if you go to Boulogne Billancourt. Very beautiful exhibitions on three floors. And very warm welcome. B.Casabianca
Interesting place, few tourists, nice building and nice surroundings. Quite a rich exhibition.
Beautiful pieces but almost nothing on the Corcovado…
